    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the gear shaft lifting fixture (ZTSE4288) to the countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302347">Figure 47</hotlnk>). Secure it with bolts from the countershaft reverse gears.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302347" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302347" filename="../figg13/G1302347.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Mainshaft &#38; Countershaft Removal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 1st-reverse and 2nd-3rd speed shift forks (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302348">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302348" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302348" filename="../figg13/G1302348.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Remove 1st - Reverse &#38; 2nd - 3rd Speed Shift Forks</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the 4th-5th speed shift fork shoes are worn, replace them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302349">Figure 49</hotlnk>). It is not necessary to remove the fork to replace the
                fork shoes.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302349" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302349" filename="../figg13/G1302349.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Replace 4th - 5th Speed Shift Fork Shoes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the 4th-5th speed shift fork, first remove the snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302350">Figure 50</hotlnk>). Push the pin through the bracket. Lift the fork from the
                unit.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302350" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302350" filename="../figg13/G1302350.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Remove Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The 5th speed gear is removed next (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302351">Figure 51</hotlnk>). The oil troughs can remain with the case.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302351" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302351" filename="../figg13/G1302351.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Remove 5th Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next place the assembly stand (ZTSE4286) on the work bench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302352">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302352" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302352" filename="../figg13/G1302352.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Assembly Stand on Work Bench</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the the assembly in the stand (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302353">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302353" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302353" filename="../figg13/G1302353.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Assembly In The Stand</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
